Class AnalyzeSkeleton2_

  • java.lang.Object
    • dend.AnalyzeSkeleton2_
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ij.gui.DialogListener, ij.plugin.filter.PlugInFilter

    public class AnalyzeSkeleton2_
extends java.lang.Object
implements ij.plugin.filter.PlugInFilter, ij.gui.DialogListener
    This class performs pruning and skeleton analysis. Modified based on AnalyzeSkeleton_.java of the ImageJ AnalyzeSkeleton_ plugin by Ignacio Arganda-Carreras.

    For more information about the original plugin, visit the AnalyzeSkeleton home page: http://fiji.sc/AnalyzeSkeleton

    Author:
    Diana Bank, Elena Zhong, Chun Han Lab, Cornell University

      • run

        public SkeletonResult run(int pruneIndex,
                          boolean pruneEnds,
                          boolean shortPath,
                          ij.ImagePlus origIP,
                          boolean silent,
                          boolean verbose)
        This method is intended for non-interactively using this plugin.

        Parameters:
        pruneIndex - The pruneIndex, as asked by the initial gui dialog.
        pruneEnds - flag to prune end-point-ending branches
        shortPath - flag to calculate the longest shortest path
        origIP - original grayscale input image (for lowest pixel intensity pruning mode)
        silent - silent run
        verbose - flag to display running information

      • run

        public SkeletonResult run(int pruneIndex,
                          boolean pruneEnds,
                          boolean shortPath,
                          ij.ImagePlus origIP,
                          boolean silent,
                          boolean verbose,
                          ij.gui.Roi roi)
        This method is intended for non-interactively using this plugin.

        Parameters:
        pruneIndex - The pruneIndex, as asked by the initial gui dialog.
        pruneEnds - flag to prune end-point-ending branches
        shortPath - flag to calculate the longest shortest path
        origIP - original grayscale input image (for lowest pixel intensity pruning mode)
        silent - silent run
        verbose - flag to display running information
        roi - points inside this region are spared from elimination when pruning end branches. ROI can be associated to a single image in the stack or all images as per ij.gui.Roi.getPosition()

      • run

        public SkeletonResult run(int pruneIndex,
                          boolean pruneEnds,
                          boolean shortPath,
                          ij.ImagePlus origIP,
                          boolean silent,
                          boolean verbose,
                          java.util.ArrayList<Edge> branches)
        This method is intended for non-interactively using this plugin.

        Parameters:
        pruneIndex - The pruneIndex, as asked by the initial gui dialog.
        pruneEnds - flag to prune end-point-ending branches
        shortPath - flag to calculate the longest shortest path
        origIP - original grayscale input image (for lowest pixel intensity pruning mode)
        silent - silent run
        verbose - flag to display running information
        branches - points inside these branches are spared from elimination when pruning end branches.

      • run

        public SkeletonResult run(int pruneIndex,
                          double thresholdLength,
                          boolean shortPath,
                          ij.ImagePlus origIP,
                          boolean silent,
                          boolean verbose)
        This method is intended for non-interactively using this plugin.

        Parameters:
        pruneIndex - The pruneIndex, as asked by the initial gui dialog.
        thresholdLength - maximum length of the branches to prune (all branches below that value are removed)
        shortPath - flag to calculate the longest shortest path
        origIP - original input image
        silent - silent run
        verbose - flag to display running information
